  <prompt>
    Deploy the Action Engine Dataverse solution (6 new entities + extension of `sprk_aichatcontextmap`), seed the default "Spaarke Assistant â€” General" playbook, and seed the 3 starter Action Templates (Summarize a matter / Send weekly task digest / Find similar matters). Use the `dataverse-deploy` skill for the solution; `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` for the playbook seed; `Seed-JpsActions.ps1` for the Templates.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior Spaarke platform engineer with Dataverse ALM expertise (PAC CLI, solution import) and familiarity with the JPS seed scripts (`Deploy-Playbook.ps1`, `Seed-JpsActions.ps1`).
  </role>

  <goal>
    Dev Dataverse environment has:
    - 6 new entities published: `sprk_action`, `sprk_actiontemplate`, `sprk_actioninstance`, `sprk_actionrun`, `sprk_toolregistry`, `sprk_gate_approval`
    - `sprk_aichatcontextmap` extension fields published
    - Default "Spaarke Assistant â€” General" playbook record present (one row in `sprk_aiplaybook`)
    - 3 starter Template records present in `sprk_actiontemplate`
    - Tool Registry rows present (â‰Ą8 per spec: 3 always-on foundational + 3 meta-tools + â‰Ą2 starter-Template-supporting Tools)
    - Azure AI Search `spaarke-resource-registry-index` populated with Tool Registry rows

    Deploy log at `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/deployments/dataverse-deploy-{date}.md`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      This is the second deploy in Phase 6. BFF is live (task 070). Now Dataverse schema + seed data lands so the Code Page (task 072) can render and the post-deploy validation (task 073) can exercise the end-to-end flow.

      Three deploy artifacts:
      1. Solution import (entities + relationships) via `dataverse-deploy` skill
      2. Playbook seed via `Deploy-Playbook.ps1`
      3. Template + Tool Registry seed via `Seed-JpsActions.ps1`
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/ActionEngine/</file>
      <file>scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1</file>
      <file>scripts/Seed-JpsActions.ps1</file>
