      <pattern name="Idempotent seed via upsert" location="scripts/Seed-JpsActions.ps1">Upsert by logical name to avoid duplicate playbook/Template rows on re-run.</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Pre-deploy check: task 060 (G1) and 070 (BFF deploy) âś… in TASK-INDEX.md; BFF endpoints reachable for any seed-script calls.</step>
    <step order="1">Read `dataverse-deploy` skill SKILL.md; review the existing seed scripts (`Deploy-Playbook.ps1`, `Seed-JpsActions.ps1`); confirm idempotency.</step>
    <step order="2">Invoke `dataverse-deploy` skill to deploy the Action Engine solution (entities + relationships + extension fields). Verify import success via PAC CLI solution list.</step>
    <step order="3">Publish all customizations: `pac solution publish` (or via Power Platform admin).</step>
    <step order="4">Run `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` for "Spaarke Assistant â€” General" playbook seed; verify exactly ONE row exists in `sprk_aiplaybook` with this name (idempotent â€” re-run safe).</step>
    <step order="5">Run `Seed-JpsActions.ps1` for the 3 starter Templates + â‰Ą8 Tool Registry rows; verify counts via PAC `pac data export` or via Web API GET on `sprk_actiontemplate` and `sprk_toolregistry`.</step>
    <step order="6">Populate the `spaarke-resource-registry-index` semantic search index: query `sprk_toolregistry` rows; for each row, push to the index with `Discoverability.semanticDescription` as the semantic field. Verify count via Azure CLI / portal.</step>
    <step order="7">Smoke test from BFF: hit a sample endpoint that depends on seeded data (e.g., GET `/playbooks/spaarke-assistant-general`); expect 200 with the seeded playbook.</step>
    <step order="8">Write deploy log at `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/deployments/dataverse-deploy-{YYYY-MM-DD}.md`: solution import result, seed row counts, search-index population count, smoke test result.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Quality gates skipped per rigor STANDARD (deploy task).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 071 status âś…. Update `current-task.md`: Dataverse seeded; ready for Code Page deploy (072).</step>
    <step order="11">Document deviations under `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
